<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Farmers Sue Over Apple Imports: A group of five Japanese growers demanded in a 
lawsuit that the Tokyo government withdraw its earlier decision to lift a ban 
on apple imports from the United States.The farmers allege that the government 
has not taken adequate precautions against the spread of fire blight, a disease 
affecting apples in the United States. The Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry 
and Fisheries decided in August to lift the ban after a bitter dispute over 
quarantine standards, which some claimed were a thinly disguised trade 
ban.After making inspections, Japan determined that U.S. apples were safe. 
</P>
