<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN SHOT TO DEATH ON FRONT PORCH BY 2 MEN IN LUXURY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old woman was fatally gunned down on her front porch near Koreatown 
on Sunday when two men yelling gang slogans from a Lexus fired at her, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said the woman was sitting outside on the porch of the house on 
South Mariposa Avenue when two men in a blue Lexus stopped and yelled gang 
slogans at her, Los Angeles police Officer Don Cox said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man in the back seat of the car opened fire with a handgun, hitting the 
woman once in the upper body, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman was taken to Los Angeles County-USC Medical Center, where she was 
pronounced dead, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Her identity was withheld pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
