WILL THAT BE PAID BY CASH OR CREDIT CARD? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THOMAS BONK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pick up the tab? Need a forklift? 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Norman on Sunday was presented a bar bill of $18,413.60, the tab for 
buying drinks at the Olympic Club for his hole in one the day before. 
</P>
<P>
 "How do you like that?" Norman said before stuffing the receipt into his 
pocket. 
</P>
<P>
 "For tax purposes," he explained. 
</P>
<P>
 Soft drinks at the clubhouse bar are $3. THOMAS BONK 
