<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Violinist Roger Wilkie has been appointed concertmaster of the Mozart Camarata 
effective Sunday; he replaces Clayton Haslop. Wilkie, who also is concertmaster 
of the Los Angeles Opera and the Long Beach Symphony, has appeared as a soloist 
with the Carmel Bach Festival Orchestra, the Santa Barbara Chamber Orchestra 
and the Los Angeles Chamber Orchestra.A founding member of the Angeles String 
Quartet, he is on the faculty of Pomona College. 
</P>
<P>
 Cirque du Soleil will hold auditions Nov. 9 to supplement its touring troupe. 
Especially sought: those with experience in modern dance or ballet, and 
athletes experienced in gymnastics, trampoline, diving, acrobatics and 
freestyle skiing. Actors, comedians and anyone with an unusual performing 
talent also are encouraged to send a resume and video cassette to Cirque du 
Soleil, 2595 Place Chasse, Montreal, Quebec, Canada, H1Y 2C3, ATTN: Casting 
Department, or a fax to (514) 527-7522. The company's production of "Alegria" 
arrives in Costa Mesa Jan. 24. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
