<P>
 Reno Air Starts Service: Reno Air will become the second discount airline to 
fly out of Orange County's John Wayne Airport on Tuesday when it starts five 
daily round-trip flights to San Jose.The carrier will add a daily nonstop to 
Reno on Thursday. The airline is taking over San Jose service from American 
Airlines, which is dropping shorter routes to concentrate on longer ones. The 
two airlines have a marketing agreement. Reno Air will compete against the 
airport's only other discount carrier, Southwest Airlines, on the San Jose 
route. 
