<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Computer Smuggling Reportedly on the Rise: The country's personal computer 
industry, already dominated by imports, is now being flooded with smuggled 
computers, the state-run Beijing Youth Daily reported.In an article titled 
"Smuggling Is Murdering China's Computer Industry," the paper said imported PCs 
now account for 60% of sales in the Chinese market. But of the imports, about 
80% to 90% are smuggled, causing tax losses of hundreds of millions of dollars, 
the paper said. The Electronics Industry ministry has notified the Customs 
House to readjust import duties on computers and other related products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
