<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Public Works Plans Outlined: The country needs to spend $500 billion in the 
next decade on public works to ease problems that are hampering economic 
development, according to official reports. Finance Minister Liu Zhongli said 
China would have to raise more funds in overseas capital markets and seek more 
loans from international financial organizations and governments, the China 
Daily said. China's investment in infrastructure last year reached about $21.4 
billion, nearly matching the entire amount invested between 1981 and 1985, the 
report said. 
</P>
