<TEXT>
<P>
 Government Issues Union Edict: All foreign-funded firms in the booming coastal 
regions have orders from Beijing to establish labor unions by the end of the 
year to safeguard workers' rights, a state-run newspaper said. The policy 
applies to all such firms that began operations before June in the coastal 
areas, which have the largest concentrations of joint ventures and other 
overseas-funded enterprises. In other regions, 60% of foreign-invested 
enterprises must begin setting up trade unions, the China Daily reported, 
quoting Yang Xinfu, vice chairman of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions. 
