<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; FORMS FOR HIGH SCHOOL EXAM DUE ON FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mail-in registration is due Friday for those wishing to take the state's high 
school proficiency exam this year.  
</P>
<P>
 A certificate of proficiency, which is equivalent to a diploma from a 
California high school, will be granted to those who pass the exam. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone 16 or older, whether enrolled in school or not, may take this exam, 
which is scheduled for Nov. 19 at 34 sites throughout the state.  
</P>
<P>
 Those younger than 16 may also take the exam, provided they have completed at 
least one semester of 10th grade.  
</P>
<P>
 People under 18 who pass the exam must have parental permission in order to 
leave school before their scheduled graduation. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange County, the exam will be given at Savanna High in Anaheim and Corona 
del Mar High in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Information kits and registration forms are available at public and private 
high schools and public libraries. JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
