<TEXT>
<P>
 Politicians, professors and other people considered experts on foreign policy 
are being given a chance to star in a new cable television program. 
</P>
<P>
 The program, "World Affairs Update With Scott Allen Gates," features 
interviews of foreign-policy experts on timely topics such as Haiti, Bosnia and 
Kuwait. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're trying to get interesting people who know about world affairs on the 
show," said Nick Mamounas, 33, the show's producer. "We're looking for anyone 
-- from educators to writers to politicians -- who has knowledge about the 
world around us." 
</P>
<P>
 The interviews are taped a month before they air in Fullerton, Placentia and 
Buena Park. Experts interested in appearing on the show are asked to call 
Mamounas at (714) 871-0603. MIMI KO 
