<P>
COMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; OCTA SEEKS IDEAS ON FULLERTON-IRVINE LINK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County Transportation Authority is asking for the public's help in 
finding ways to improve transportation. 
</P>
<P>
 Public comments are being sought to help OCTA decide whether a rail or other 
high capacity transportation system should be built for a 28-mile-long corridor 
stretching from Fullerton to Irvine, passing through Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 OCTA officials will be deciding what type of system -- bus, rail or special 
car-pool lanes -- should be considered, where the system should go and whether 
it will be underground. 
</P>
<P>
 A decision is expected to be made in early 1996 and the third in a series of 
public meetings on the subject is set for Wednesday at 4:30 p.m. at Irvine City 
Hall, 1 Civic Center Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call OCTA spokeswoman Elaine Beno at (714) 560-5571. MIMI KO 
