<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LAKE FOREST; PLANNERS' VOTE ALLOWS BUSINESS PARK EATERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city Planning Commission has approved a zoning change that will allow 
restaurants in the Pacific Commercenter business park. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the plan approved last week, the 824,000-square-foot business park, 
located at Bake Parkway and Trabuco Road, would be allowed 20,000 square feet 
for restaurant use.The proposed zone change will go to the City Council for 
final approval. 
</P>
<P>
 The increase was part of a deal between Los Alisos Development Co. and the 
city that reduced the amount of space in the business park dedicated to 
businesses that attract traffic, such as health clubs, banks and travel 
agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 City planners said the 20,000 square feet of restaurant space would 
accommodate one sit-down dining establishment and as many as two drive-through, 
fast-food restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
 The project will not modify any essential conditions under which the Pacific 
Commercenter was approved. 
</P>
<P>
 The modification drew few complaints from three neighboring homeowners' 
associations. City planners did agree to hold additional public hearings when 
specific plans for the restaurants are turned in. 
</P>
<P>
 Several conditions were imposed to ease the project's impact on neighboring 
homeowners, including restrictions on when trash can be collected and a 
requirement for at least a 190-foot setback from any residential dwelling. 
</P>
<P>
 A traffic study commissioned by Los Alisos Development Co. concluded that the 
restaurants would not significantly increase traffic in the area. City staff 
reviewed the study and agreed with its conclusions. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
