<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FULLERTON; FLORY, BANKHEAD WIN POLICE PAC BACKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Political Action Committee of the Fullerton Police Officer's Assn. has 
announced its endorsement of two City Council candidates in the Nov. 8 
election. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Danny Becerra said the committee chose to endorse Councilwoman Jan M. 
Flory and former Councilman Don Bankhead, who recently was forced to leave 
office after a recall election. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee had sent out a questionnaire to all candidates and interviewed 
the few who responded, Becerra said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The basis for our endorsement is we felt (Bankhead and Flory) best represent 
the interests of the Police Department," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bankhead, 62, is a retired police captain who worked for the Fullerton Police 
Department for more than 31 years. Flory, 50, is an attorney. 
</P>
<P>
 Other candidates still in the race are: Jack Dean, 46; incumbent Conrad 
Dewitte, 46; Bob McNutt, 50; Michael J. Mummert, 35; Gary Nouskajian, 43; Edith 
O'Donnell, 65; Stuart Stitch, 25; James J. Tanaka, 37, and Carole E. Wink, 55. 
</P>
<P>
 Dick Logemann, Leland C. Wilson, Bahia E. Wilson and Michael J. Wagner have 
withdrawn from the race. MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
