<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY SCHOOL BOARD CANDIDATES; COMMUNITY COLLEGE DISTRICTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All four of the county's community college districts will hold elections. The 
districts are trying expand education programs in an era of tight budgets and 
want to get residents more involved in college programs. COAST 
</P>
<P>
 Boundaries: Serves Costa Mesa, Fountain Valley, Garden Grove, Huntington 
Beach, Midway City, Newport Beach, Seal Beach, Stanton, Sunset Beach and 
Westminster 
</P>
<P>
 Enrollment: 53,000 
</P>
<P>
 Facilities: Coastline Community College, Golden West College, Orange Coast 
College, KOCE-TV (Public Broadcasting System affiliate station) 
</P>
<P>
 Issues: District must cope with cuts in state funding. It is also attempting 
to expand vocational and technical programs to match job market. Officials want 
to reduce administrative costs. 
