<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORK CREW CLEANS HUNTINGTON OIL LEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A work crew spent Sunday attempting to clean up about 750 gallons of crude oil 
that leaked from an underground pipe into the gutter of a Huntington Beach 
street, a fire official said. 
</P>
<P>
 The leak was discovered at 5 p.m. Saturday near a sidewalk at 1717 Huntington 
St., the official said. 
</P>
<P>
 The crew began the cleanup at 9 p.m. Saturday, the official said, and the area 
is expected to be completely cleaned sometime today . 
</P>
</TEXT>
