<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA YOUTH DIES OF SHOT IN NECK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teen-ager was fatally shot in the neck outside a Santa Ana apartment complex 
early Sunday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Federico Ceja Ibarra, 18, was found at 1:48 a.m. lying in front of an 
apartment on South Standard Ave., Santa Ana Police Sgt. Brian Collins said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The shooting was the result of some kind of fracas inside the apartment," 
Collins said. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Collins, someone called police and said a man had come into an 
apartment with a rifle and shot another man in the leg. 
</P>
<P>
 But when police arrived, they found Ibarra, who lived on the same street as 
the complex, with a gunshot in the neck, Collins said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ibarra was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Because witnesses said Ibarra was associated with a local gang, the shooting 
is being investigated by the Police Department's gang detail, Collins said. 
</P>
