<HEADLINE>
<P>
19 DRIVERS ARRESTED AT SOBRIETY CHECK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nineteen people spent the night in Laguna Beach's city jail after being 
stopped late Saturday and early Sunday at a field sobriety checkpoint and 
arrested on suspicion of drunk driving, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 1,300 motorists passed through the checkpoint set up on eastbound lanes 
of the 20000 block of Laguna Canyon Road between 10 p.m. Saturday and 2:30 a.m. 
Sunday, said Sgt. Mike Hall of the Laguna Beach Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 1,084 motorists were stopped, questioned and given an informational 
brochure and 38 of them were given a field sobriety test, Hall said. Of the 19 
drivers who failed the test and were arrested, 14 were men and five were women, 
Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspected drunk drivers were released starting at 7 a.m. Sunday, a 
department spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
