<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROAD CLOSED AFTER FIRE SYSTEM FAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Torrey Road south of Piru was closed late Sunday after a fire-fighting system 
at a Unocal Corp. propane pumping station failed, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 California Highway Patrol officers sealed off the roadway south of Telegraph 
Road (California 126) as a precaution after a water deluge system failed about 
8:45 p.m., a Fire Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 It was not immediately known how much -- if any -- gas had escaped from the 
company's Torrey Hill Pump Station at 3824 Guiberson Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Department officials dispatched a hazardous materials team to the scene 
to determine why the system failed and if gas had escaped from the plant. 
</P>
<P>
 No injuries were reported in the incident. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
